  "A meteorologist runs an ensemble of 50 model simulations for an approaching winter storm. If 45 of the 50 runs predict heavy snow while 5 predict rain, the forecaster should communicate:": "",
  "Equal probability of snow and rain since both outcomes appeared in the ensemble": "",
  "There is no way to predict whether it will snow or rain": "",
  "High confidence in heavy snow, with a small possibility of rain, since the vast majority of ensemble members agree on the snow scenario": "",
  "That the model is broken because not all runs agree": "",
  "When 90% of ensemble members agree on an outcome, forecasters can communicate high confidence in that scenario while acknowledging the small probability of the alternative, giving the public useful information about both the most likely outcome and the uncertainty involved.": "",
